Description: Contactless payments transforming how people pay / get paid.
Headquarters Regions: Greater San Diego Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: The way we make payments is changing. According to new research, in-store contactless payments are expected to reach $8 trillion in 2022*. Digital payments are being made with mobile phones, wearables and more. The range of pay-enabled devices will keep growing. Right now, giants like Apple, Google and Samsung enable contactless payments, but only on their devices – and tokenization is only available on their platforms. Jib is opening up the landscape. Our solution can turn any object, from sunglasses to snowboard gloves, into a secure payment device. Jib Technologies is a San Diego-based financial technology (FinTech) startup enabling brands like Shell Oil Company, Feld Entertainment and Cubic Transportation Systems to engage and reward their audience through co-branded and contactless payments while fostering financial inclusion for 1.7 billion adults who remain unbanked. Jib is changing the way people pay and get paid by offering our Payments-as-a-Service infrastructure platform enabling brands to know their audience better through real-time purchase data. Powered by Jib, any business now has the ability to send real-time payments directly to an employee’s or customer’s mobile wallet via QR code, SMS/text, email or any messaging app such as WhatsApp. *Coronavirus has significantly accelerated contactless payment adoption.

Description: An electric 3 wheel vehicle with steer by wire technology pioneering a new segment in urban mobility
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Helix Motors devised a thrilling, affordable and practical solution to the problem of urban mobility.  Imagine if a vehicle was half the width of other traditional automobiles, yet was still safe, quick, beautiful, zero emission…and affordable.  That is precisely what Helix Motors has created. Data shows that 90% of all daily commutes and 78% of all driving occurs with just 1 occupant in a vehicle.  So, most of society is simply buying too large a vehicle for its daily needs.  What inhibited mass adoption was the lack of stability in high speed braking and turning maneuvers, that problem is solved by a vehicle that leans into a turn and Helix’s patented solution solves that problem in a modern electronic way similar to aircraft systems. The vehicle is a 3 wheel vehicle that tilts into the turns like a motorcycle or jet fighter using an electronic “steer by wire” system applied from the aircraft industry.  The design represents a new form factor which is twice as efficient as other electric vehicle solutions due to its size (we are calculated to realize over 300 MPGe).  The vehicle is designed to hold two people, one in front of the other, at a comfort level equal to a BMW 6 series sedan.

Description: Las Vegas Sun is a local online news publication which is committed to journalism and public service.
Headquarters Regions: Western US
Full Description: Las Vegas Sun is a local online news publication, which is committed to journalism and public service while continuing to provide quality coverage of breaking news, business, entertainment, local sports, and best political analysis. In 1949, the Review-Journal locked out members of the printing union. As a result, the International Typographical Union began its own newspaper on May 3, 1950, but struggled financially. The International Typographical Union then turned to Hank Greenspun. On May 21, 1950, Greenspun published his first edition as Las Vegas Free Press. In July of that year, the name was changed from the Las Vegas Free Press to the Las Vegas Sun. Las Vegas Sun is the first media organization that won the top awards in all three journalism areas of print, online, and broadcast. In 2009, it won the Pulitzer Prize for Public Service, journalism’s most prestigious award, for its investigation of construction deaths on the Las Vegas Strip and the failures of government, management, and labor unions to protect workers. It was also the first print-based news organization to win Columbia University's duPont Award.  Las Vegas Sun was first published in 1950 by Hank Greenspun.
Industry Groups: Content and Publishing, Media and Entertainment

Description: SCF Arizona offers worker’s compensation solutions to clients in Arizona.

Full Description: SCF originally was part of the Industrial Commission of Arizona. The Arizona Legislature provided seed money for SCF, which was paid back by 1938. Since that time, SCF Arizona has been funded entirely by policyholders' premiums and by investments. SCF receives no state funds and is not tax supported. In 1969, the Arizona Legislature separated SCF from the Industrial Commission, allowing SCF to begin operating as a private business. The Legislature continued to cut ties with SCF in 1983, when it exempted the company from following state procurement rules under Title 35. In 1990, a further separation occurred, when the Legislature removed SCF from the state personnel and state risk management systems. And in 2004, a Maricopa County Superior Court Judge ruled that SCFâ€:tm:s fiduciary duty is to its policyholders and not to the State of Arizona. SCF is fully competitive and operates under the same rules, rate structure and regulations as all private insurance companies providing workersâ€:tm: compensation insurance in Arizona. In 2007, SCF Arizona launched SCF Premier Insurance Company, a wholly owned subsidiary that gives the company more flexibility in premium rates for SCFâ€:tm:s largest and safest companies. Through all the changes, SCFâ€:tm:s vision and mission remain focused on quality customer service to all policyholders and on providing unsurpassed excellence in workersâ€:tm: compensation.
